node.text:
It’s finally here! My full tanning tutorial filled with all my favorite tips & tricks to achieve a flawless self tan! Code JUSTUS10 saves you💰on any @glowprotans order. Answering some FAQs below!
.
💕How long does your tan last?
- Mine lasts about 4-5 days!
💕How often do you reapply?
-I reapply once a week!
💕How long does a bottle of the self tanner last you?
-I get about 12-15 tans out of each bottle.
💕How do you tan your back?
-I ask my husband to tan mine. If you don’t have anyone, glowpro sells a back tanning applicator on their website!
💕Will my tan transfer on my clothes or sheets?
-I recommend wearing dark long clothing to sleep in! However if the instant bronzer does transfer on your clothes or bedding, it washes right out!
.
I hope this was helpful! Let me know if you have any more questions!

node.text: I make guacamole to keep around the house almost every week! I usually add a dollop to my burger bowls, chicken and rice, annd anything else it sounds good one. node.text: 🤣🤣 I couldn’t help myself

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Rachelle Justus (CPT) on August 16, 2021 tagging @fashionnova. May be an image of 1 person and outdoors.

node.text:
Cabo was too good to me. It was so nice to get away for a few days and relax. I often get asked if I track macros while on vacation. Most of the time, no. However if I have a goal I’m working towards and want to keep chipping away, then I’ll track!
.
One of my favorite parts of traveling and vacation is trying all the yummy foods. It took me a while to find that *balance* when it comes to being mindful yet still enjoying myself. I always make sure to prioritize protein with every meal, still incorporate veggies, & if I have a dessert or “fun” food, I will eat until I’m satisfied and not stuffed. It’s okay to let loose and enjoy yourself 🙌🏻 I just make sure to hop right back on track once I get home 🥦🥗🫐
